[{"question":"Margaret, what did you make of that?","answer":"Look, I think Rob Portman acted in a way that was consistent with the love for his son and also consistent with a movement that\u0027s happening across the country with Republican legislators.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":52,"aSentId":53},{"question":"David Bossie, is what Senator Portman did a good thing or a bad thing?","answer":"Well, look, I think it\u0027s obviously what he thinks is the right thing for his family.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":64,"aSentId":65},{"question":"So what would you do if one of your children came to you and said, \"Dad, I\u0027m gay\"?","answer":"Well, look, I have very small children, so I\u0027m -- years --","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":77,"aSentId":78},{"question":"They are going to grow up, right?","answer":"Well, we hope so, yes.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":79,"aSentId":80},{"question":"One second there you say do something wrong, would be the fact they were born gay be something they had done wrong?","answer":"Well, you believe -- you may believe that people can be born gay.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":85,"aSentId":86},{"question":"But you would try to correct the wrong, as you put it?","answer":"No.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":89,"aSentId":90},{"question":"OK, what would you advise Senator Portman to do?","answer":"I would have advised Senator Portman to show unconditional love for his child but not -- not abandon his principles, which he has espoused the last many years.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":104,"aSentId":105},{"question":"Margaret?","answer":"So what I would offer David is a fourth consideration.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":106,"aSentId":107},{"question":"At point will you move with the time?","answer":"Just one second, I don\u0027t make decisions, I\u0027ll be candid with you, we don\u0027t make public policy decisions in the conservative moment based on what the latest poll says.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":120,"aSentId":121},{"question":"So, is that what this is all about?","answer":"Well, I mean, Piers, I hate to use your own tool against you, but you just cited polling.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":135,"aSentId":136},{"question":"Let me just say this, do you think, Piers, it would bad thing for all potential rapists to think the woman they are about to rape would be armed and wouldn\u0027t bad way to stop a potential rape?","answer":"Here is the problem, Mr. Bossie, to facilitate that logical extension of thought process, every single woman in America needs to walk around with a gun.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":145,"aSentId":146},{"question":"How do they know when they\u0027re going to rape?","answer":"A rapist has to think that the woman may be armed that\u0027s all it takes.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":149,"aSentId":150},{"question":"How do they know when they are going to be attacked by a rapist?","answer":"They do know if you disarm everyone in America, they do know you are not armed.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":152,"aSentId":153},{"question":"That seems to fly in the face of your argument?","answer":"Well, it doesn\u0027t there are criminals and there are people who obviously, Piers, violate 30 or 40 federal laws long before they murder somebody.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":164,"aSentId":165},{"question":"How many times have you been properly in love in your life before you met Rita?","answer":"Once.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":201,"aSentId":202},{"question":"In terms of the defense, how are they positioning the defense now, in light of what these witnesses have been saying?","answer":"That\u0027s very good question.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":222,"aSentId":223},{"question":"Why do you care so passionately about this case?","answer":"There were allegations in town there could possibly be a cover-up, the media wasn\u0027t providing much coverage about the case, and so, I wrote about it.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":243,"aSentId":244},{"question":"What do you think of the developments in the last 24 hours?","answer":"I think it\u0027s very important, Piers, that the two witnesses testified that they actually saw both defendants involved in digital penetration of this young woman\u0027s vagina, which is rape --","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":268,"aSentId":269},{"question":"How significant do you think that aspect to this case is, the fact that these two are star football players in a town that\u0027s football crazy?","answer":"Well, I think, you know, you can\u0027t blame an entire town for what a bunch of kids did.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":280,"aSentId":281},{"question":"NTERVIEWER: You weren\u0027t thinking that a girl who keeps repeatedly throwing up was pretty drunk?","answer":"No, because it\u0027s natural.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":290,"aSentId":291},{"question":"You see that a lot?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":292,"aSentId":293},{"question":"At parties?","answer":"Not just at parties.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":294,"aSentId":295},{"question":"People throwing up because they had too much to drink?","answer":"Yes, you can see that anywhere.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":299,"aSentId":300},{"question":"But in terms what they said there about a culture of drunkenness and so on, could that play against this girl in the sense she got so drunk, a variety of parties that she didn\u0027t know what was going on?","answer":"Well, Piers, the defense, of course, is trying to pierce holes in the issue of whether or not she was drunk.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":304,"aSentId":305},{"question":"So, what do we do now?","answer":"I\u0027m gonna put you on the stand.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":322,"aSentId":323},{"question":"I get to tell my story?","answer":"It means they get to tear you apart.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":324,"aSentId":325},{"question":"So, you know, they would argue, I guess, well, look, both sides don\u0027t agree because it is a dramatization?","answer":"I believe that is a dramatization.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":354,"aSentId":355},{"question":"How long was it before he finally told you?","answer":"I think it was a week or two, as I remember.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":429,"aSentId":430},{"question":"Where do you feel you get the strength to be like this?","answer":"Well, first of all, I\u0027m almost 74.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":447,"aSentId":448},{"question":"What could be better?","answer":"But let\u0027s, Valerie, take a break.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":450,"aSentId":451},{"question":"Why not?","answer":"I\u0027m serious.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":459,"aSentId":460},{"question":"If I could replay a moment for you now, what would you choose?","answer":"Oh, my goodness, my husband telling me that he thought we should adopt.","docId":"130315pmt","qSentId":509,"aSentId":510}]